  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This prospective randomized is designed to evaluate the safety and efficacy of hernia repairs
      using local anesthesia compared with those using general anesthesia for patients with
      incarcerated hernia.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      The outcome parameters measured included intraoperative conditions, postoperative conditions
      and long-term follow-up conditions.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
